  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But at least they go where you can observe them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, what happens when the deportations happen, this is when, when the thing becomes just very, very, very obvious to my father.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father has a fairly good set of connections, which suggest that the deportations to Poland, in fact, may be death camps, although nobody knows that for sure.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Nobody really wants to believe it anyway because letters still keep coming back.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Turns out that in 1942, the President of the Slovak Republic, Monsignor Tiso, who is a collaborator, institutes a special kind of-- what's called a presidential exemption program, which protects certain Jews from deportation.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's what's called a white card.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
